iliation overwrites story statuses without checking git history or proof documents.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74.\n- All 74 stories across 17 epics are complete. No stories to execute.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Write: 1, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 6 times today\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":5,"newStart":1,"newLines":19,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27"," ","+### Session 15 — state corruption fix #7 (2026-03-27T18:35Z)","+","+- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and previous session fixing this.","+- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.","+- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.","+- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml.","+- Root cause persists: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. This is the 7th occurrence today.","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: ~12","+- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1","+- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads","+- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 7th time","+"," ### Session 14 — state corruption fix #6 (2026-03-27T18:31Z)"," "," - Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` despite committed `done` state and proof docs in git."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
